# Firebase Admin SDK Configuration for MRP Pipeline
# The pipeline needs Admin SDK credentials to write to Firestore

# METHOD 1 (RECOMMENDED): Service Account JSON File
# -----------------------------------------------------
# 1. Go to Firebase Console: https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Select project 'valmet-buyer'
# 3. Go to: Project Settings > Service Accounts > Generate New Private Key
# 4. Download the JSON file
# 5. Save it as 'firebase-service-account.json' in this directory
# 6. Add to .gitignore to keep it secure

# Optional: Use a different filename
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=path/to/your/service-account.json

# METHOD 2 (ALTERNATIVE): Individual Environment Variables
# ----------------------------------------------------------
# If you prefer environment variables over JSON file:
# FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=valmet-buyer
# FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY_ID=your-private-key-id-here
# FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYour private key here\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
# FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx@valmet-buyer.iam.gserviceaccount.com
# FIREBASE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id
# FIREBASE_CERT_URL=https://www.googleapis.com/robot/v1/metadata/x509/firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx%40valmet-buyer.iam.gserviceaccount.com

# NOTE: VITE_* credentials in .env are for the frontend app and won't work for the pipeline
